Investors are concerned about the implications of the political turmoil on France's budget. Meanwhile, France's government is facing collapse, and its cooperation with Chad has ended. One headline highlights the selection of Charles Kushner as the new US Ambassador to France. Despite the turmoil, President Macron took the world on a tour of the restored Notre-Dame cathedral, demonstrating his leadership and commitment to France's cultural heritage. The Economist presents a broader perspective, noting that France is not the only country facing fiscal challenges. Finally, Rotary International reports on the personal connections and family reunions that can be fostered in France.

name: Jared Isaacman
summary: Former President Donald Trump has nominated Jared Isaacman, an entrepreneur and private astronaut, to lead NASA. Isaacman is a billionaire who made his fortune in the payment processing industry. He has also founded a space exploration company called Shift4 Payments. Isaacman was chosen over several other candidates, including former NASA astronauts and current NASA officials. The nomination has been met with mixed reactions. Some experts have praised Isaacman's business acumen and his commitment to space exploration. Others have expressed concern about his lack of experience in government and his ties to SpaceX, a private space company founded by Elon Musk.
